---
name: scljet-write-overflow
description: SclJet M3 cell-overflow writer — large payloads spill onto overflow-page chains (cross-backend)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet cell-overflow writer

[ByteSlice, byteSliceToList, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildOverflowTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)

```scalascript
// Build "a" * n with log-depth recursion so the JS lane (no TCO) does not blow
// the stack while producing multi-KB payloads.
def text(n: Int): String =
  if n <= 0 then ""
  else if n == 1 then "a"
  else
    val half = text(n / 2)
    if n % 2 == 0 then half + half else half + half + "a"

// The 1016-char row lands on the local = m = 39 branch: its ~39-byte local
// portion stays on the single 512-byte leaf and the remainder spills onto a
// two-page overflow chain (page 1 = schema, page 2 = leaf, pages 3-4 = the
// chain). Reference `integrity_check` accepts the file and both values read
// back byte-exact. (Kept to 4 pages so the JS lane's per-byte `byteSliceToList`
// stays within Node's stack; longer chains are exercised on the int lane.)
val rows: List[List[SqliteValue]] = List(
  List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText(text(1016))),
  List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("tail")))

buildOverflowTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(n INTEGER, v TEXT)", rows) match
  case Right(bytes) => println((bytes.length / 512).toString + ":" + byteSliceToList(bytes).toString)
  case Left(error) => println("ERROR:" + error.message)
```
